{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Create financial penalties for property buyers who pull out of purchases",
        "additional_details": "Buyers pulling out after submitting an offer can have huge financial implications for sellers, and affect people's mental health.\r\n \r\nBuyers should only be able to pull out of a sale if there is a good reason, such as serious faults being found following an inspection, not just because they change their mind or find another property.\r\n",
        "background": "We want the Government to impose financial penalties on property purchasers who pull out of a purchase after submitting a final offer, unless there is a good reason. The fine should be paid to the seller.",
